      "body": "<!--e57a25ab6845829454e8d69fc972939a-->\n\nThe following sections might be updated with supplementary metadata relevant to reviewers and maintainers.\n\n<!--006a51241073e994b41acfe9ec718e94-->\n### Code Coverage & Benchmarks\nFor details see: https://corecheck.dev/bitcoin/bitcoin/pulls/35444.\n<!--021abf342d371248e50ceaed478a90ca-->\n### Reviews\nSee [the guideline](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#code-review) for information on the review process.\n| Type | Reviewers |\n| ---- | --------- |\n| Concept ACK | [pablomartin4btc](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/35444#pullrequestreview-4464278390), [hebasto](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/35444#pullrequestreview-4465420475) |\n\nIf your review is incorrectly listed, please copy-paste <code>&lt;!--meta-tag:bot-skip--&gt;</code> into the comment that the bot should ignore.\n<!--174a7506f384e20aa4161008e828411d-->\n### Conflicts\nReviewers, this pull request conflicts with the following ones:\n\n* [#bitcoin-core/gui/872](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/gui/pull/872) (Menu action to export a watchonly wallet by achow101)\n* [#35445](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/35445) (wallet, descriptor: Revert `StringType::COMPAT` for Miniscript expressions and drop the concept of a Descriptor ID that can be validated by achow101)\n* [#35436](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/35436) (wallet: Add addHDkey interface by pseudoramdom)\n* [#35302](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/35302) (Silent Payments:  Sending (take 2) by Eunovo)\n* [#35201](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/35201) (Refactor: Updated signMessage to use util::Expected and removed SigningResult::OK by kevkevinpal)\n* [#34993](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34993) (wallet: `NotifyCanGetAddressesChanged` when advancing `next_index` by davidgumberg)\n* [#34969](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34969) (fuzz: several improvements to scriptpubkeyman harness by brunoerg)\n* [#34520](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34520) (refactor: Add [[nodiscard]] to functions returning bool+mutable ref by maflcko)\n* [#32489](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/32489) (wallet: Add `exportwatchonlywallet` RPC to export a watchonly version of a wallet by achow101)\n* [#30343](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/30343) (wallet, logging: Replace WalletLogPrintf() with LogInfo() by ryanofsky)\n\nIf you consider this pull request important, please also help to review the conflicting pull requests. Ideally, start with the one that should be merged first.\n<!--5faf32d7da4f0f540f40219e4f7537a3-->\n### LLM Linter (✨ experimental)\n\n\n\nPossible places where named args for integral literals may be used (e.g. `func(x, /*named_arg=*/0)` in C++, and `func(x, named_arg=0)` in Python):\n\n- `WalletDescriptor(std::move(desc), creation_time, 0, 0, 0)` in `src/wallet/external_signer_scriptpubkeyman.cpp`\n\n\n\n<sup>2026-06-02 16:33:46</sup>\n",
