        "name": null,
        "patch_url": null
      },
      "body": "I think removing the external lock here is fine now that `GetWalletDescriptor()` and `GetDescriptorString()` are self-locking. One subtle difference is that the descriptor metadata and descriptor string are now read under two separate locks instead of one caller-held lock. I don’t see an issue because descriptor state should not normally change concurrently here, but I wanted to double-check that no atomicity across these two reads was intended.\n",
